abstract: Florence Fabricant shares details on the New York openings she’s most excited about.
snippet: Florence Fabricant shares details on the New York openings she’s most excited about.
lead_paragraph: Fall is a time for fresh starts, and there’s something satisfying about seeing veteran chefs break out with restaurants of their own. That’s why Frenchette and Scampi are among the places I’m most looking forward to this season.

abstract: Sharon Horgan and Rob Delaney pick up where they left off in Season 3 of the deliriously filthy comedy “Catastrophe.” And “Dear White People” becomes a TV series.
snippet: Sharon Horgan and Rob Delaney pick up where they left off in Season 3 of the deliriously filthy comedy “Catastrophe.” And “Dear White People” becomes a TV series.
lead_paragraph: “Catastrophe” returns for a third season in the delightfully smutty marriage between the alter egos of Sharon Horgan and Rob Delaney. And “Dear White People” brings Justin Simien’s film about race relations in academia to television — and survives.

abstract: As editorial board member and columnist, Mr. Wilkins sometimes felt he had to train his fight against racism on the institution that employed him.

lead_paragraph: Roger Wilkins would not be trifled with.
